The paper deals with the Count-Sketch algorithm, which is commonly used in data streaming and heavy hitters problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also presents improved concentration bounds for the algorithm, which involves analyzing the covariance matrix and using median-of-median-of-medians argument, indicating that it may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of the algorithm for l_2 recovery of exactly k-sparse estimates, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SI (Signal Processing) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents simulations of the algorithm on a power law distribution, indicating that it may also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category.
